## JMeter JSON Filtering

### Problem
Need to extract information from JSON response only if a condition is met: `$.cart.cart_state == "PENDING"`

### Solution: JSON Extractor with Conditional Filter

#### JSON Path Expressions

For filtering based on cart_state:

```json
// Extract cart_id only when cart_state is PENDING
$.cart[?(@.cart_state=='PENDING')].cart_id

// Extract cart_number only when cart_state is PENDING
$.cart[?(@.cart_state=='PENDING')].cart_number

// Extract entire cart object only when cart_state is PENDING
$.cart[?(@.cart_state=='PENDING')]

For NOT COMPLETED filter:

// Extract when cart_state is NOT COMPLETED
$.cart[?(@.cart_state!='COMPLETED')].cart_id

// Multiple conditions (PENDING or MODIFIED)
$.cart[?(@.cart_state=='PENDING' || @.cart_state=='MODIFIED')].cart_id

JMeter Configuration

JSON Extractor Settings:

Names of created variables: cart_id
JSON Path expressions: $.cart[?(@.cart_state=='PENDING')].cart_id
Match No.: 1
Default Values: NOT_PENDING

