Troubleshooting Large Exports
Issue: Getting fewer results than expected

Check actual count:

curl -X POST "https://your-es-host/your-index-*/_search" \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -u "user:pass" \
  -d '{
    "size": 0,
    "track_total_hits": true,
    "query": {
        "bool": {
            "filter": [
                {"range": {"@timestamp": {"gte": "...", "lte": "..."}}}
            ]
        }
    }
}' | python3 -m json.tool | head -30

Look for:

"hits": {
    "total": {
        "value": XXXXX,
        "relation": "eq"
    }
}

Common Query Patterns
Match specific values

{
    "query": {
        "terms": {
            "status": ["COMPLETED", "MODIFIED"]
        }
    }
}

Date range filter

{
    "query": {
        "range": {
            "@timestamp": {
                "gte": "2024-01-01",
                "lte": "2024-12-31"
            }
        }
    }
}

Multiple conditions

{
    "query": {
        "bool": {
            "must": [
                {"match": {"operation": "CREATE"}},
                {"match": {"email": "test@example.com"}}
            ],
            "filter": [
                {"range": {"@timestamp": {"gte": "...", "lte": "..."}}}
            ]
        }
    }
}

Exclude fields

{
    "query": {
        "bool": {
            "must_not": [
                {"exists": {"field": "test_flag"}}
            ]
        }
    }
}

Getting Query from Kibana
Steps to extract exact query:

    In Kibana Discover, apply your filters
    Click “Inspect” button (top right, looks like <>)
    Click “Request” tab
    Copy the JSON query
    Use it in your curl/Python script

Key differences between Kibana UI and API queries:

    Kibana uses match_phrase for exact matches
    Use .keyword suffix for exact string matches
    Check track_total_hits: false - set to true to get accurate counts
    Kibana might search multiple indices with wildcards

Tips & Best Practices
For Large Exports (>1M records):

    Use scroll timeout of 10m or more

    ?scroll=10m

    Increase batch size

    ?size=10000

    Track progress

    if [ $((COUNTER % 100000)) -lt 10000 ]; then
        echo "Progress: $COUNTER records..."
    fi

    Use wildcards for date-based indices

    index-name-*

    Extract only needed fields

    "_source": ["field1", "field2"]

Field Path Examples

For nested fields:

"_source": ["metadata.cart_id"]

Accessing in output:

hit['_source']['metadata']['cart_id']

Performance Considerations

    Scroll context timeout: 10m is usually sufficient
    Batch size: 10,000 is optimal (don’t go higher)
    Network: Export from same region as ES cluster
    Time: ~5-15 minutes for 1-2M records

