Common Errors & Solutions
Error: index_not_found_exception

    Check index name spelling
    Use wildcard pattern: index-*
    Verify index exists in Kibana

Error: scroll context not found

    Increase scroll timeout
    Reduce time between scroll requests
    Check cluster health

Error: Getting 0 results

    Verify field names (check with Kibana Inspect)
    Use .keyword for exact matches
    Check date format matches

macOS: grep: invalid option -- P

    Use Python for JSON parsing instead of grep
    Or install GNU grep: brew install grep

Summary
For JMeter:

    Use JSON Path with filter syntax: $.cart[?(@.field=='value')]
    Extract to variables, then use JSR223 PostProcessor for logging

For Elasticsearch:

    Use scroll API for large datasets
    Get exact query from Kibana Inspect
    Use Python scan helper or bash with curl
    Always use track_total_hits: true to verify counts

